column57: The overall returns of the equity graph are quite good,
So yes I would invest in this stratergy, as the risk is low
Yes, all 3 stratergies shorted the spread, which resulted in a loss
A news filter is not a bad idea however I personally feel that the threshold should be extremely high for such filters
Cause if the news filter starts capturing the over-reaction which dosen't sustain for the longer term, it would make our strategy less useful
So any filters should work only in extreme cases and should not be driven by short term human emotion
Pros would be that it prevents us from crashing in an actual long term diversion
Cons would be it might act on false positive news and reduce our profits
